  • Class
    Description
    Boots
    This represents the boots object that the player can collect in the game.
    Characters
    Represents a moving character in the game (Enemy or the Player).
    Door
    This represents the Door that the player can interact (by unlocking using a key) in the game
    EffectOnPlayer
    Represents the effect that occurs when the player enters a tile or interacts with something.
    Enemy
    Represents an enemy character in the game.
    ExitTile
    Represents the tile where the player enters to exit the level (A sub class of Tile).
    FireTile
    Represents the fire tile in the game.
    FloorTile
    Represents the base floor tile in the game.
    ForceFloor
    Represents the force floor tile ingame.
    Game
    This represents the main game logic.
    IceTile
    Represents the Ice tile in the game.
    Inventory
    This represents the inventory of the player in the game
    Item
    Represents the general items in the game that the player can collect.
    Key
    This represents the key that the players can interact and use in the game
    Level
    This represents the levels of the game, containing the visual layout of the map per level and all the other interactive elements.
    Maps
    This represents the game map containing the tiles, doors, and inventory items to be picked up.
    Microchip
    This represents the microchips that the player can collect in the game
    Player
    Represents the Player of the game itself
    TeleportTile
    Represents the Teleport tile in the game.
    Tile
    This represents the tiles and its different types seen in the game map.
    WallTile
    Represents the wall tile in the game.
    WaterTile
    Represents the Water tile in the game.
